A vintage 1950s style illustration of a single ornate golden birdcage with its door wide open, sitting on an antique wooden workbench surrounded by scattered mechanical gears, springs, and clockwork components. Inside the cage, a small mechanical bird made of brass and copper sits on a perch, while an identical mechanical bird flies freely outside, trailing tiny golden sparks. The warm sepia-toned background features faded blueprint patterns of intricate machinery. The scene conveys liberation through clever engineering, with dramatic shadows cast by warm amber workshop lighting.
